Name: shadowPos

Details:

Syntax:

Types:

Function:

Synopsis:

Description:
Determines the positions of shadows. The shadow postion can also be set for separate dimensions by hshadowPos and vshadowPos.

Note that:
* `shadowPos(n)` is equivalent to `shadowPos(n, n)`.
* `shadowPos(hs, vs)` is equivalent to `hshadowPos(hs), vshadowPos(vs)`.


Also see [shadow] and [shadowColor].

Examples:
<figure s1.png 250x150>
box1 = box(size(200,100), shadow(true), shadowPos(50,50), resizable(false));
render(box1);
</figure>
![s1](s1.png)

<warning>Shadow not taken into account for size computation</warning>

